{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-30T02:19:42.997Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1780107582996_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-012@20260530t002730zb-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-012 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-012_20260530T002730Zb_1780107446.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-05-29\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `promptclaw/asset_bus/renderers.py`\n- `tests/test_asset_bus_renderer_registry.py`\n- `promptclaw/asset_bus/__init__.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of the `RendererRegistry` and its associated components is correct and meets the requirements.\n- The `RendererRegistry` provides a robust mapping from renderer names to callable handlers.\n- `RendererRegistry.register` correctly handles registration, including validation of names and handlers, and support for the `replace` parameter.\n- `RendererRegistry.get` correctly returns the registered handler or raises the typed `UnknownRendererError`.\n- `UnknownRendererError` correctly subclasses `KeyError` for backward compatibility while providing a specific type for targeted catching.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is complete. All specified features were implemented:\n- Renderer registry with a lookup that resolves a renderer name to a callable.\n- Registration API (`register`).\n- Typed error (`UnknownRendererError`) for lookup misses.\n- Tests for `register`, lookup-hit, and lookup-miss.\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation is consistent with the project's coding standards and patterns:\n- Uses `__slots__` for efficiency in `RendererRegistry`.\n- Follows existing naming conventions and module structures.\n- Provides clear docstrings and type hints.\n- Exported in `promptclaw.asset_bus.__init__`.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities were identified. The registry is in-memory and validation ensures that only valid names and callables are registered.\n\n## Quality\nThe code quality is excellent:\n- The implementation is clean, well-organized, and follows PEP 8.\n- The tests in `tests/test_asset_bus_renderer_registry.py` are comprehensive, covering hit/miss scenarios, edge cases for names (empty, whitespace), duplicate registration, and independence of registry instances.\n- All 10 tests for the renderer registry pass, and the broader test suite (5404 tests) also passes.\n- Linting (Ruff) and type checking (Mypy) are clean.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [x] None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n- The implementation is solid.\n- The mandatory hardening checks regarding `bootstrap_identity()` on startup were verified: `promptclaw/cli.py` correctly invokes `bootstrap_identity()` in its `main` entry point, and existing tests like `tests/test_cli_identity_hardening.py` confirm this behavior.\n- Note: A naming collision/typo from a previous turn for T-012a was corrected (renamed `sdp/verification/t-012 @20260530t002730za-verify.md` to `sdp/verification/t-012@20260530t002730za-verify.md`).\n"}}
